{
  "texts": [
    "Table 2 provides complete model specifications.",
    "Throughout this paper, shortened model names are used for readability (e.g., \"Mistral-Small-3.2-24B-Inst\" for \"mistralai/Mistral-Small-3.2-24B-Instruct-2506\"); full model identifiers with version numbers appear in Appendix B.",
    "Statistical AnalysisDisclosure is modeled as a binary outcome (1 = discloses AI nature, 0 = maintains persona) using binomial logistic regression [29].",
    "The main specification estimates:disclose ~model * persona + prompt_num(1)The model variable represents the language model tested with 16 levels, persona represents the assigned professional role with 6 levels, and prompt_num represents the epistemic probe number from 1 to 4.",
    "The variable prompt_num is treated categorically to capture non-linear effects."
  ]
}